        <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Hd1e108">Rubrica 7</head>
        <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De voluntario et inuoluntario</head>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e114">
          <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
          ¶ De voluntario et inuoluntario. Rubrica. 7.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e119">
          <lb ed="#V" n="65"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e116">ARistoteles ethicorum
            <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>li. 3 c. 3</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>
          <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e127">Uoluntarium videbitur vtique esse cuius
            <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>principium in ipso est. Sciente 
            singu<lb ed="#V" n="69" break="no"/>laria in quibus est operatio: Beatus 
            qui<lb ed="#V" n="70" break="no"/>dem nullus nolens est. Uirtus voluntarium est
            <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>nihil minus et malitia voluntarium est. 
            Uolun<lb ed="#V" n="72" break="no"/>tarie sunt virtutes: etenim habituum sunt concau
            <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>se.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e144"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e142">/ Li. 5. c. 7</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e146">Dico voluntarium quod aliquis
          <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>in seipso existentium sciens et non ignorans 
          ope<lb ed="#V" n="75" break="no"/>ratur. Iustum operari omne voluntarium est. 
          Ledi<lb ed="#V" n="76" break="no"/>tur quidem vtique aliquis nolens: et iniusta 
          pati<lb ed="#V" n="77" break="no"/>tur. Iniustum patitur nullus nolens.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e159"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e159">/ Idem 
          ma<lb ed="#V" n="78" break="no"/>gnorum moralium li. i. c. 17.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e161">Uidetur secundum 
            virtu<lb ed="#V" n="79" break="no"/>tem et malitiam esse voluntarium.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e169"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e172">/ c. 18.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e171">
          Uo<lb ed="#V" n="80" break="no"/>luntarium est quod operamur non coacti. 
          Ope<lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>ratis ex necessitate sequitur tristitia. Operatis
          <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>vero per concupiscentiam delectatio sequitur.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e181"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e186">/ c.
          <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e183">Iniustum facientes nolentes iustum faciunt.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e189">
          <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e199">/ c. 64.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e193">Iusta et iniusta operantur volentes. 
            Ne<lb ed="#V" n="85" break="no"/>mo voluntarius ledi sustinet.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e199"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e209">/ Idem 
          re<lb ed="#V" n="86" break="no"/>thori li. i. c. 18.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e201">Uolentes faciunt quecumque 
            scien<lb ed="#V" n="87" break="no"/>tes et non coacti.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e209"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e222">/ c. 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e211">Uoluntas est cum ratione
          <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>appetitus: nullus enim vult nisi cum 
          putaue<lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>rit esse bonum. Irrationalis autem appetitus ira <!--82.xml-->
          <pb ed="#V" n="28-r"/>
          <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
          <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>et concupiscentia.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e229"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e244">/ Lib. 2. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e231">Nullus ea quae 
          si<lb ed="#V" n="2" break="no"/>bi apparent inpossibilia appetit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e237"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e254">/ c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e239">
          Pu<lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>gnantes contraria videntur velle.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e245"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e264">/ ca. 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e247">Acu
          <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>te sunt voluntates iuuenum et non magne</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e253"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e274">/ c. 19</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="5"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e255">Nullus inpossibilia affectat neque concupiscit
            <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>vt in pistolibus. Omnes cum potentes velint agunt</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e263">
          <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e288">/ Idem politicorum libro 5. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e267">Que volunt 
            poten<lb ed="#V" n="8" break="no"/>tes agunt omnes.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e273"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e298">/ Idem de anima. li. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e275">
          Uolun<lb ed="#V" n="9" break="no"/>tas appetitus est.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e282">
          <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e311">¶ Terentius in heutontumerumeno. c. 17.</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="11"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e286">Nulla est tam facilis res quin difficilis fiet
            <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>quam inuitus faciat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e294">
          <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e325">¶ Tullius retho. artis noue li. 2. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e298">
            Uolun<lb ed="#V" n="14" break="no"/>tario facinori nulla est excusatio: 
            impruden<lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>tie et iusta depraecatio parata est.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e306"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e337">/ Idem 
          phi<lb ed="#V" n="16" break="no"/>lippicorum libro 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e308">Nolite velle quod fieri non potest.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e314">
          <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e350">¶ Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum lib. 7. e. 8.</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="18"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e318">Da operam ne quid vnquam inuitus facias. Quic
            <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>quid futurum est necesse est futurum 
            repugnan<lb ed="#V" n="20" break="no"/>ti. In volentem necessitas non est. Qui imperia 
            li<lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>bens excipit partem acerbissimam seruitutis 
            ef<lb ed="#V" n="22" break="no"/>fugit. Non qui iussus aliquid facit miser est:
            <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>sed qui inuitus facit. Sic animum componamus
            <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>vt quicquid res exigit id velimus.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e337"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e373">/ Lib. 8.
          <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>e. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e339">Nihil honestum est quod ab initio quid a 
            coa<lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>cto fit. Omne honestum voluntarium est.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e347"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e386">/ Li. 13
          <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>e. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e349">Animo et beneficia et iniurie constant.</quote> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e394">/ Li. 16
            <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>c. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e399">Actio recta non erit: nisi recta fuerit
              <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>voluntas. Ab hac enim actio est.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e360"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e408">/ Idem de
          <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>moribus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e362">Omne peccatum actio est voluntaria.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e368">
          <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e421">¶ Lex diges. ti. de iurisdi. om. iud. l. si. per 
            er<lb ed="#V" n="32" break="no"/>rorem:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e372">Non consentiunt qui errant. Quid enim
              <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>tam contrarium est consensui quam error qui 
              imperi<lb ed="#V" n="34" break="no"/>tiam detegit.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e382"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e436">/ Ti. de pactis. l. i. in prin.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e384">Quid
          <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>tam congruum est fidei humane quam ea que in
          <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>ter eos placuerunt seruare.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e392"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e448">/ Lex codi. ti. ad
          <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>le cor. de sic. l. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e394">Crimen committitur si et 
            volun<lb ed="#V" n="38" break="no"/>tas nocendi intercedat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e402">
          <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e463">¶ Ualerius maximus lib. 9. c. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e406">Error non
            <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>sua sponte: sed vanis incitatus imaginibus
            <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>culpe se implicat.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e414">
          <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e477">¶ Boetius de consolatione lib. 4. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e418">Duo
            <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>sunt quibus humanorum actuum constat effectus:
            <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>voluntas scilicet et potestas: quorum si alterum desit
            <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>nihil est quod explicari queat.<!--82.xml-->
            <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
          </quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e433">
          <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e498">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum li. i. e. 37</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e437"> Non est
            <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>beneficium quod praestatur inuitis: nec cuiquam vtile
            <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>quod aduersa voluntate conceditur.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e445"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e510">/ Li. 4. e. 7.</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="49"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e447">Iniquum est vt hominis vitio deputetur quod eius 
            vo<lb ed="#V" n="50" break="no"/>luntate non regitur.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e455"> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e522">/ Libro. 5. e. 39.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e457">
          Suspe<lb ed="#V" n="51" break="no"/>ctum est quod patiuntur nolentes: nam hoc est re 
          ve<lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>ra beneficium si sine murmure feratur acceptum.</quote>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-d1e465">
          <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>
          <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e536">¶ Isidorus in sinonima soliloquiorum lib. 2.</ref>
          <lb ed="#V" n="54"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e469">Nihil potest caro facere nisi quod voluit animus</quote>
          <lb ed="#V" n="55"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Rd1e546">¶ Andreas ad gualterium de amore li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d20988-Qd1e548">
            Ma<lb ed="#V" n="56" break="no"/>ioribus censetur meritis dignus qui bona 
            spon<lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>tanee pegit: quam qui ea coactus exercuerit.</quote>
        </p>
      </div>
